title: [Gyldemar Forest, Winding Trail]
description: The trees thin out as the trail slopes up toward a nearly sheer cliff face to the north.  Insects flit through the air, their soporific drone the only sound audible aside from the wind through the boughs above.

The trees thin out as the trail slopes up to the north, their branches barely meeting over the widened path.  Nocturnal insects flit through the air, their soporific humming the only sound audible aside from the wind through the boughs above.
